# NovaLang Lesson Format 3.0

Format name: NovaLang Lesson Format 3.0
Status: `APPROVED_FOR_IMPLEMENTATION_PENDING_OWNER_RUNTIME_FREEZE`
Reference implementation: ja-daily_life-m01-u1-l1
Approved by project owner: 2026-07-15
Supersedes: `.cursor/rules/03_novalang_lesson_format_2_0.mdc` (Q14 only)
Related: ADR-008 (Golden Reference Lesson), ADR-012 (Q14 Real-World Practice
redesign), ADR-014 (Unit Comprehensive Conversation placement correction,
distinct from Q14)

## Authority, priority, and versioning

This file is the Single Source of Truth for the **Q14 behavior** of the
opt-in `lessonFormat: five_cards` format. Apply workspace rules in this
order:

1. `AGENTS.md`
2. `.cursor/rules/novalang.mdc` (Core Rules; the workspace has no
   `01_novalang_core.mdc`)
3. This file, for any question about Q14 behavior
4. `.cursor/rules/03_novalang_lesson_format_2_0.mdc`, for every other part of
   the format (Q1–Q13, five cards, access plans, persistence, result page,
   etc.), which remains the Single Source of Truth for everything it defines
   except the parts explicitly superseded below
5. `.cursor/rules/02_novalang_lesson_standard.mdc`

Only the project owner can change this specification. This is a breaking
change to Q14 only — it does not silently edit or reinterpret Format 2.0.
Format 2.0 remains the historical record of what was approved on 2026-07-13
and is not rewritten; it is marked superseded for Q14 by an explicit note in
that file (see below) rather than by deleting or altering its Q14 section.

